It would be good to have the bulk of wrap and unwrap in BaseHolder... but I'm struggling to think of how to do this nicely... as getBeans needs a real type.   Maybe we could pass it that type and have a common wrapper function interface:
    private T wrap(T item, Class<? extends WrapperFunction<T>> wrapperType)
￼    {
￼        ServletContextHandler contextHandler = getServletHandler().getServletContextHandler();
￼        if (contextHandler != null)
￼        {
￼            for (WrapperFunction<T> wrapperFunction : contextHandler.getBeans(wrapperType))
￼            {
￼                item = wrapperFunction.wrapEventListener(item);
￼            }
￼        }
￼        return item;
￼    }
Note sure if that works.... or if it is better... thoughts?

